; form-ontology-loader.fk — bootstrap ontology bindings without runtime JSON parsing.
;
; The Form-owned `bp` floor below carries the reviewed bootstrap rows needed by
; the current source runner, source compiler, and grammar capsules. It keeps
; direct source from relying on the old fkwu identity stub, where `(bp "add")`
; returned the string "add" instead of a NodeID. The full blueprint registry
; still needs to move into Form data; until then this loader admits the rows
; that are actually exercised by the Form stdlib and fails loudly for the rest.
;
; Prelude requirement: make_nodeid, node_type, node_inst, intern_node,
; intern_trivial_string, intern_trivial_int, walk_recipe_here, list/cons/head/
; tail/len/empty, str_concat, form_error, and str_eq are available from the
; kernel/core prelude.
;
; --src surface seam (2026-07-17): on fkwu, every requirement above resolves
; EXCEPT walk_recipe_here — the top-level engine-defn walk (the one call at
; the foot of this file, which would install the bmf-context-key-* /
; bmf-locale-* constant family for engine.fk) is a sibling-kernel native
; with no fkwu counterpart or bp coordinate. Under fresh `fkwu --src` that
; one call stays loud (unresolved, axiom-5 recovery) and the generated
; constants stay ungenerated; engine.fk records the same seam from the
; consumer side. Recorded, not shimmed: a numb walk would silently skip the
; generation it claims.

;; --- source-compiler tables ----------------------------------------
;; FORM-CATEGORY-TABLE and FORM-PRIMITIVE-TABLE keep the source compiler's
;; historic (name type inst) shape. Their coordinates come from the bootstrap
;; bp table below, not from a host-generated runtime table.

(defn fol-bp-row (name pkg level ty inst)
    (list name pkg level ty inst))

(let FOL-BP-BOOTSTRAP-TABLE
